  "text": "LG 2 [CITATION_1] again maintaining the total power in each mode and the value of I 0 to be consistent with that in Eq's.9 and 13. The azimuthal mode number is directly proportional to the OAM per photon in the beam while the radial mode number p indicates the number of concentric donut rings (p + 1) introduced by the generalized Laguerre polynomial L | | p . For the purpose of this study, we will only focus on fitting LG modes with p = 0 as we are only interested in an approximate first order fit. We introduce the mode scaling factor η, and define a new beam waist parameter w LG which is proportional to the beam waist of the Gaussian beam through the relationship,",
